  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/6740",
  "title": "feat(chat): add custom toggle button support",
  "body": "**Summary**\r\n\r\nThis PR:\r\n- adds a prop `toggleButtonComponent` that allow passing a custom toggle button component to the chat UI component.\r\n- forwards that prop for the React InstantSearch chat widget.\r\n- adds two templates (`toggleButton.layout` and `toggleButton.icon`) for the InstantSearch.js chat widget.\r\n\r\nOne issue I currently see is that when using a custom toggle button component, you would need to pass `pointer-events: all;` on your custom button because we use `pointer-events: none;` on the `.ais-Chat` wrapper.\r\nShould we pass this style in the Chat UI component if we detect a custom `ToggleButtonComponent` is used?\r\n\r\n```ts\r\nconst CustomToggleButtonComponent = (props) => {\r\n  return (\r\n    <button style={{ pointerEvents: 'all' }} {...props}>\r\n      Toggle Chat\r\n    </button>\r\n  );\r\n};\r\n\r\n<Chat\r\n  /* ... */\r\n  toggleButtonComponent={CustomToggleButtonComponent}\r\n/>\r\n```",
  "created_at": "2025-10-09T09:26:40Z",
